[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pensioner dies in A75 accident near Gatehouse of Fleet

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An elderly man has died in a single-vehicle crash on the A75 in Dumfries and Galloway.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were sent to the accident near Gatehouse of Fleet at about 11:50.
Police said a 76-year-old man driving a Renault Scenic died at the scene of the crash.
The road was closed for several hours while collision investigation work continued and a lengthy diversion route put in place.
Drivers were advised to avoid the area if at all possible.
Anyone with information about the crash has been asked to contact police.
